The paper discusses deep learning and regularization techniques for autoencoders to discover and represent factors of variation beyond those relevant for categorization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on image datasets and manipulation of images, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI.
